---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PlusExpand from "@components/illustrations/icons/PlusExpand.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQs | Elizabeth Armstrong Therapy" description="Frequently asked questions about therapy with Elizabeth Armstrong, LMFT. Learn about sessions, fees, insurance, and what to expect.">

  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Questions & Answers</p>
      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Everything you might want to know about working together. If you don't see your question here, please reach out.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Content -->
  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container container-narrow">

      <!-- Getting Started Section -->
      <div class="faq-section" id="getting-started">
        <h3>Getting Started</h3>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              How do I schedule a first appointment?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>The first step is scheduling a free 15-minute consultation. This gives us a chance to talk briefly about what brings you to therapy and whether we might be a good fit. You can request a consultation through my <a href="/contact.html">contact page</a> or by calling (949) 444-3899.</p>
                <p>If we decide to move forward, we'll find a time for your first full session. I typically have availability within 1-2 weeks.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What happens in the first session?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>Our first session is about getting to know each other. I'll ask questions about what brings you to therapy, your history, and what you're hoping to get out of our work together. You'll also have space to ask me anything you'd like.</p>
                <p>There's no pressure to share everything at once. We'll move at a pace that feels comfortable for you. By the end of the session, we'll have a sense of direction and can discuss how often we might meet.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              How do I know if you're the right therapist for me?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>The relationship between therapist and client is one of the most important factors in successful therapy. That's why I offer a free consultation, so you can get a sense of me before committing.</p>
                <p>Pay attention to how you feel during our conversation. Do you feel heard? Comfortable? Like you could open up to me? It's okay if you're nervous (that's normal), but you should feel a basic sense of connection and trust.</p>
                <p>If after a few sessions you feel we're not the right fit, I'm happy to help you find another therapist who might be better suited to your needs.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Logistics Section -->
      <div class="faq-section" id="logistics">
        <h3>Logistics</h3>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              How long are sessions?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>Individual therapy sessions are 50 minutes. Couples sessions are typically 75-90 minutes, and family sessions range from 60-90 minutes depending on the needs of the family.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              How often will we meet?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>Most clients meet weekly, especially at the beginning of therapy. This frequency helps build momentum and allows us to work more deeply. As therapy progresses and you're feeling more stable, we may shift to every other week or monthly sessions.</p>
                <p>Ultimately, the frequency is something we'll decide together based on your needs, goals, and circumstances.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              Do you offer telehealth sessions?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>Yes! I offer secure video sessions for clients anywhere in California. Telehealth makes therapy more accessible and fits into busy lives. Many clients find it just as effective as in-person work.</p>
                <p>I use a HIPAA-compliant platform to ensure your privacy. All you need is a private space, a reliable internet connection, and a device with a camera.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What is your cancellation policy?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>I ask for at least 24 hours' notice if you need to cancel or reschedule. Late cancellations or missed sessions are charged the full session fee.</p>
                <p>I understand that emergencies happen. If something truly unexpected comes up, please reach out and we can discuss.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Fees & Insurance Section -->
      <div class="faq-section" id="fees">
        <h3>Fees & Insurance</h3>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What are your fees?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>Individual therapy sessions (50 min): $175</p>
                <p>Couples therapy sessions (75-90 min): $225</p>
                <p>Family therapy sessions (60-90 min): $200</p>
                <p>I offer a limited number of sliding scale spots for those who need them. If cost is a barrier, please mention it during our consultation and we can discuss options.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              Do you accept insurance?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>I am an out-of-network provider, which means I don't bill insurance directly. However, if you have out-of-network benefits, you may be able to receive partial reimbursement for our sessions.</p>
                <p>I can provide you with a superbill (a detailed receipt) that you can submit to your insurance company for potential reimbursement. I recommend contacting your insurance provider to ask about your out-of-network mental health benefits before we begin.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What forms of payment do you accept?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>I accept credit cards, debit cards, and HSA/FSA cards. Payment is due at the time of the session.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What is a Good Faith Estimate?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>Under the No Surprises Act, you have the right to receive a "Good Faith Estimate" explaining how much your care will cost. This estimate is based on the information we have at the time and may change as treatment evolves.</p>
                <p>I will provide you with a Good Faith Estimate before we begin therapy. If you have questions about this, please don't hesitate to ask.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- About Therapy Section -->
      <div class="faq-section" id="about-therapy">
        <h3>About Therapy</h3>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What is narrative therapy?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>Narrative therapy is based on the idea that we make sense of our lives through stories. The stories we tell about ourselves, often shaped by our families, culture, and experiences, influence how we see ourselves and what we believe is possible.</p>
                <p>In narrative therapy, we work to understand the stories that have been shaping your life, separate you from the problems you're facing (you are not the problem), and discover alternative stories that align with your values and hopes.</p>
                <p>It's a respectful, non-pathologizing approach that honors your expertise on your own life.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              How long does therapy take?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>There's no fixed timeline for therapy. Some people come for a few months to work through a specific issue; others engage in longer-term work to address deeper patterns. It depends on your goals, your situation, and how quickly things shift.</p>
                <p>We'll check in regularly about how you're feeling and whether therapy is meeting your needs. You're always in control of when to continue and when to end.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              Is what I share in therapy confidential?
              <PlusExpand class="faq-icon" />
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <div class="faq-answer-content">
                <p>Yes, confidentiality is fundamental to therapy. What you share stays between us, with a few legal exceptions that I'll explain fully before we begin (such as imminent risk of harm to yourself or others, or suspected abuse of a child or vulnerable adult).</p>
                <p>For couples and family therapy, we'll discuss confidentiality boundaries at the start so everyone understands how information will be handled.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Crisis Information -->
      <div class="crisis-callout">
        <h4>Important: Crisis & Emergency Information</h4>
        <p>
          Therapy is not appropriate for crisis situations. If you are in immediate danger or experiencing a mental health emergency, please take one of the following steps:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Call 988</strong> (Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, available 24/7)<br>
          <strong>Call 911</strong> or go to your nearest emergency room<br>
          <strong>Text HOME to 741741</strong> (Crisis Text Line)
        </p>
        <p>
          Please do not use email or my contact form to communicate urgent matters, as I may not see messages immediately.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Band -->
  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Still have questions?</h2>
      <p>
        I'm happy to answer any questions you have. Reach out for a free consultation and we can talk.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact.html" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get in Touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
